as people think I am.

726
00:29:30,281 --> 00:29:32,116
Well, I don't know what to tell you.

727
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:33,742
I don't know anything about art.

728
00:29:33,826 --> 00:29:36,036
No one knows anything about art.
Why'd you buy it?

729
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:37,788
I don't know.

730
00:29:37,872 --> 00:29:40,249
It's been a while since
I'd gone shopping.

731
00:29:43,212 --> 00:29:46,756
I walked in that sad little room,

732
00:29:46,840 --> 00:29:49,926
in the back…
the one nobody seemed to care about,

733
00:29:50,010 --> 00:29:55,265
and everywhere I looked,
there was color and life.

734
00:29:55,349 --> 00:29:58,310
Something the front
room was a little short of.

735
00:29:58,394 --> 00:30:00,895
And then suddenly she caught my eye.

736
00:30:00,979 --> 00:30:04,316
I thought, "I know her. She has a secret.

737
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:07,277
She knows a joke that I don't."

738
00:30:07,361 --> 00:30:12,490
I thought, "Maybe if I take her
home, she'll tell me the joke."

739
00:30:12,574 --> 00:30:14,994
And that made me smile.

740
00:30:19,999 --> 00:30:22,251
[STUBS OUT CIGARETTE]

741
00:30:22,335 --> 00:30:24,337
All right.

742
00:30:33,096 --> 00:30:35,098
Secret door.

743
00:30:36,641 --> 00:30:38,476
Like Houdini.

744
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:40,478
MIDGE: This isn't where
you store the bodies

745
00:30:40,562 --> 00:30:43,190
of the people who try to
buy your paintings, is it?

746
00:30:50,906 --> 00:30:53,909
This is the painting.

747
00:30:53,993 --> 00:30:57,413
I've heard the stories. [CHUCKLES]

748
00:30:59,498 --> 00:31:06,004
So tell me… does it make you smile?

749
00:31:06,088 --> 00:31:10,634
It's the most beautiful
thing I've ever seen.

750
00:31:10,718 --> 00:31:13,096
I mean, it's so different from…

751
00:31:13,180 --> 00:31:14,847
My other work.

752
00:31:14,931 --> 00:31:16,683
Yes. No.

753
00:31:16,767 --> 00:31:20,061
I mean, your other work is wonderful.

754
00:31:20,145 --> 00:31:22,814
Probably wards off
vampires, but this one…

755
00:31:22,898 --> 00:31:26,442
This one is perfect.

756
00:31:26,526 --> 00:31:27,985
But I don't understand.

757
00:31:28,069 --> 00:31:30,405
Why would you keep
it locked away in here?

758
00:31:30,489 --> 00:31:32,907
I mean, why don't you sell it?

759
00:31:32,991 --> 00:31:35,660
Sell it?

760
00:31:35,744 --> 00:31:39,622
Sell the greatest thing I'm
ever gonna do in my lifetime?

761
00:31:39,706 --> 00:31:42,584
Stick it in a gallery and
a doctor'd bring it home.

762
00:31:42,668 --> 00:31:44,294
A museum, then.

763
00:31:44,378 --> 00:31:47,172
Oh, yeah, what, next to the mummies?

764
00:31:47,256 --> 00:31:49,341
People should see this.

765
00:31:49,425 --> 00:31:51,719
No, I painted this for me.

766
00:31:53,805 --> 00:31:56,557
This was gonna hang in my home.

767
00:31:56,641 --> 00:31:58,642
When I had a home.

768
00:31:58,726 --> 00:32:01,895
And a family, when I had that life.

769
00:32:01,979 --> 00:32:04,982
This was… this was gonna go there.

770
00:32:06,984 --> 00:32:09,194
But that was then.

771
00:32:09,278 --> 00:32:11,405
And this is now.

772
00:32:11,489 --> 00:32:13,658
I will never have that life.

773
00:32:13,742 --> 00:32:16,453
-Now, wait…
-I'm not trying to spin a melodrama.

774
00:32:16,537 --> 00:32:17,787
I'm being very realistic.

775
00:32:17,871 --> 00:32:20,123
The chance for that life is gone.

776
00:32:20,207 --> 00:32:21,916
That's ridiculous.

777
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:27,756
It'll never happen because…
everything I have,

778
00:32:27,840 --> 00:32:31,384
I put into that.

779
00:32:31,468 --> 00:32:34,012
Nothing left.

780
00:32:34,096 --> 00:32:37,223
-I think that's very sad.
-Well, that's the way it is.

781
00:32:37,307 --> 00:32:43,105
If you… if you want to do something great

782
00:32:43,189 --> 00:32:47,902
you want to take
something as far as it'll go…

783
00:32:50,989 --> 00:32:54,366
You can't have everything.

784
00:32:54,450 --> 00:32:59,914
You lose… family.

785
00:32:59,998 --> 00:33:02,000
Sense of home.

786
00:33:04,419 --> 00:33:09,424
But then… look at what exists.

787
00:33:14,555 --> 00:33:17,974
Are you sure I can't get
you to sleep with me?

788
00:33:18,058 --> 00:33:20,310
Nope.

789
00:33:20,394 --> 00:33:23,230
Even after I told you
my sad, lonely story?

790
00:33:23,314 --> 00:33:27,192
I mean, my God, that
was my very best line.

791
00:33:29,361 --> 00:33:32,447
-[DOOR OPENS IN DISTANCE]
-BENJAMIN: Hello?

792
00:33:32,531 --> 00:33:35,116
-[DOOR CLOSES]
-Miriam? Where are you?

793
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:37,536
The doctor sounds panicked.

794
00:33:37,620 --> 00:33:40,914
I should go.

795
00:33:40,998 --> 00:33:43,835
Miriam?

796
00:33:43,919 --> 00:33:46,171
You never saw this.

797
00:33:48,173 --> 00:33:51,509
That's too bad.

798
00:33:51,593 --> 00:33:53,595
Miriam?

799
00:33:57,098 --> 00:33:59,642
Tell him to pick out
any painting he wants.

800
00:33:59,726 --> 00:34:01,352
Leave a check on the table.

801
00:34:01,436 --> 00:34:03,187
But don't tell me where he lives,

802
00:34:03,271 --> 00:34:05,273
or I'll come back and get it.

803
00:34:14,784 --> 00:34:16,786
[SHIP HORN BLOWS IN DISTANCE]

804
00:34:21,374 --> 00:34:24,334
-Where did this come from?
-I always hide a few for you.

805
00:34:24,418 --> 00:34:26,169
Thanks.

806
00:34:26,253 --> 00:34:29,214
Mmm.

807
00:34:29,298 --> 00:34:31,633
-How's Mom?
-Asleep.

808
00:34:31,717 --> 00:34:33,260
-Are you sure?
-I put the mirror under her nose.

809
00:34:33,344 --> 00:34:34,803
Yeah, well, you have to after last time.

810
00:34:34,887 --> 00:34:36,388
[LAUGHS]: I know.

811
00:34:36,472 --> 00:34:38,891
[LAUGHS]: Five seconds
away from burying her alive.

812
00:34:38,975 --> 00:34:40,893
She was so mad. [LAUGHS]

813
00:34:40,977 --> 00:34:42,854
You ever notice that, in
every one of these pictures,

814
00:34:42,938 --> 00:34:45,106
I'm standing three feet away
from the rest of the family,

815
00:34:45,190 --> 00:34:46,524
and you're crying?

816
00:34:46,608 --> 00:34:50,194
Well, I suppose every
family thinks they're the worst.

817
00:34:50,278 --> 00:34:52,655
Yeah, but ours has photographic proof.

818
00:34:52,739 --> 00:34:54,449
TESS: Stand-up comedy?

819
00:34:54,533 --> 00:34:56,451
Who knows from stand-up comedy?

820
00:34:56,535 --> 00:34:58,369
You do remember I've
been working in a club

821
00:34:58,453 --> 00:35:00,038
-for 16 years, right?
-Yeah, but I thought

822
00:35:00,122 --> 00:35:01,998
that was, like, singers,
jugglers, dog acts,

823
00:35:02,082 --> 00:35:04,459
that sort of stuff. Stand-up comedy?

824
00:35:04,543 --> 00:35:05,960
[CHUCKLES] I'll be damned.

825
00:35:06,044 --> 00:35:07,503
This girl, she's amazing.

826
00:35:07,587 --> 00:35:09,380
I have a whole plan set up for her.

827
00:35:09,464 --> 00:35:11,466
I mean, it's all there.
I just need a little money.

828
00:35:11,550 --> 00:35:13,552
Why?
Do you have to pay the clubs or something?

829
00:35:13,636 --> 00:35:15,304
No, but we have to get to the clubs.

830
00:35:15,388 --> 00:35:16,805
We have to tour.

831
00:35:16,889 --> 00:35:18,849
I need a car; you
can't tour without a car.

832
00:35:18,933 --> 00:35:21,101
Well, doesn't your
comic friend have a car?

833
00:35:21,185 --> 00:35:24,063
No.
She's got, like, 40,000 hats but no car.

834
00:35:24,147 --> 00:35:26,190
Geez. Dilemma.

835
00:35:26,274 --> 00:35:29,693
-How are you doing?
-Oh, you know, terrible.

836
00:35:29,777 --> 00:35:33,364
The house is falling apart.
Skint leaves his leg everywhere.

837
00:35:33,448 --> 00:35:35,699
Mom could find booze in a nunnery.

838
00:35:35,783 --> 00:35:38,827
Literally, she broke
into a nunnery last week.

839
00:35:38,911 --> 00:35:41,246
I did start flirting
with the delivery boy

840
00:35:41,330 --> 00:35:43,667
from the grocery, though;
he's got a wooden leg, too.

841
00:35:43,751 --> 00:35:47,253
-Well, you have a type.
-I do. Huh.

842
00:35:47,337 --> 00:35:48,964
You think there's any
chance Leopold and Loeb

843
00:35:49,048 --> 00:35:50,966
are gonna agree to let me sell that land?

844
00:35:51,050 --> 00:35:53,594
-Nope.
-Yeah.

845
00:35:55,596 --> 00:35:57,473
Shit.

846
00:36:02,936 --> 00:36:04,938
-What's this?
-Keys to Mom's car.

847
00:36:05,022 --> 00:36:07,232
There's no way Mom's
gonna let me drive her car.

848
00:36:07,316 --> 00:36:09,109
When she took me to school, I walked,

849
00:36:09,193 --> 00:36:10,568
and she drove alongside me.

850
00:36:10,652 --> 00:36:13,030
I'll tell her it was stolen, by a nun.

851
00:36:13,114 --> 00:36:14,449
You sure?

852
00:36:16,701 --> 00:36:18,285
The highlight of my day

853
00:36:18,369 --> 00:36:21,247
is thinking up different
ways to kill my husband.

854
00:36:21,331 --> 00:36:23,290
One of us needs a win.

855
00:36:23,374 --> 00:36:26,252
Thanks, sis.

856
00:36:29,255 --> 00:36:32,717
-Beat him to death with his leg?
-I'll put it on the list.

857
00:36:35,011 --> 00:36:37,388
[CROWD SINGING IN HEBREW]

858
00:36:37,472 --> 00:36:39,808
[SINGING CONTINUES]

859
00:36:43,562 --> 00:36:45,772
-I'm starving.
-Don't think about it.

860
00:36:45,856 --> 00:36:47,816
I've been thinking about
it since dinner yesterday.

861
00:36:47,900 --> 00:36:49,735
-Shh.
-We've been without food for 24 hours.

862
00:36:49,819 --> 00:36:52,404
Some people never have
anything but bread soaked in water.

863
00:36:52,488 --> 00:36:54,781
Oh, that sounds delicious.

864
00:36:54,865 --> 00:36:57,284
[SINGING ENDS]

865
00:36:57,368 --> 00:36:59,411
For the sin which we
committed before you…

866
00:36:59,495 --> 00:37:01,329
I noticed your kid's
been stuffing candy bars

867
00:37:01,413 --> 00:37:03,623
in his face the entire ceremony.

868
00:37:03,707 --> 00:37:05,417
-Moishe.
-His face is covered in chocolate.

869
00:37:05,501 --> 00:37:06,752
He looks like Al Jolson.

870
00:37:06,836 --> 00:37:08,670
Be quiet. We are in temple.

871
00:37:08,754 --> 00:37:10,756
That's right, and everyone
can see that we're talking,

872
00:37:10,840 --> 00:37:12,592
because these seats are fabulous.

873
00:37:12,676 --> 00:37:15,595
-If only they were edible.
-Did you see Mara Weinstock?

874
00:37:15,679 --> 00:37:17,388
-Six rows back.
-RABBI: For the sin

875
00:37:17,472 --> 00:37:19,057
which we have committed before you

876
00:37:19,141 --> 00:37:21,017
-committed before you…
-That's Catholic, Astrid.

877
00:37:21,101 --> 00:37:22,935
I just don't understand
why he gets to eat.

878
00:37:23,019 --> 00:37:24,520
I don't understand why you get to sit.

879
00:37:24,604 --> 00:37:26,272
The elder can sit, rabbi said.

880
00:37:26,356 --> 00:37:28,441
We are the same age, and I'm standing.

881
00:37:28,525 --> 00:37:31,360
Well, good for you.
You get to be king of the Jews.

882
00:37:31,444 --> 00:37:33,196
How'd that work out for the last guy?

883
00:37:33,280 --> 00:37:35,281
And for the sin which we
have committed before you

884
00:37:35,365 --> 00:37:36,741
by a gathering of lewdness.

885
00:37:36,825 --> 00:37:39,494
Has anyone ever had her diagnosed?

886
00:37:39,578 --> 00:37:41,496
She's the only one actually praying here.

887
00:37:41,580 --> 00:37:42,831
ETHAN: More chocolate, please.

888
00:37:42,915 --> 00:37:45,042
Try aiming for your mouth, kid.

889
00:37:45,126 --> 00:37:47,127
That's his third candy bar,
in case you weren't counting.

890
00:37:47,211 --> 00:37:49,171
He's four.
A four-year-old shouldn't have to fast.

891
00:37:49,255 --> 00:37:50,881
Not till he's bar mitzvah'd.

892
00:37:50,965 --> 00:37:53,717
When I was a boy, I fasted.
And you know why I fasted?

893
00:37:53,801 --> 00:37:56,303
Because we had nothing!

894
00:37:56,387 --> 00:37:58,180
Every day was Yom Kippur.

895
00:37:58,264 --> 00:38:00,474
Moishe, please. I'm atoning.

896
00:38:00,558 --> 00:38:04,144
For the things I'd
like to do to that man,

897
00:38:04,228 --> 00:38:06,063
-I apologize.
-That's right, sweetheart,

898
00:38:06,147 --> 00:38:08,816
let it out.

899
00:38:08,900 --> 00:38:10,567
For the sin which we
have committed before you,

900
00:38:10,651 --> 00:38:13,238
-by false denial and lying.
-And for the sin which we…

901
00:38:13,322 --> 00:38:15,824
Shirley, your mother
is tipping over again.

902
00:38:15,908 --> 00:38:17,951
Oh, it's okay, I tied her to the bench.

903
00:38:18,035 --> 00:38:19,619
And for the sin which we
have committed before you

904
00:38:19,703 --> 00:38:20,829
by eating and drinking.

905
00:38:20,913 --> 00:38:23,123
For the sin which we committed before you

906
00:38:23,207 --> 00:38:25,041
by embezzlement.

907
00:38:25,125 --> 00:38:28,086
And for the sins which we
incur the penalty of the four forms

908
00:38:28,170 --> 00:38:31,339
of capital punishment,
executed by the Court:

909
00:38:31,423 --> 00:38:35,844
stoning, burning,
decapitation and strangulation.

910
00:38:35,928 --> 00:38:38,221
RABBI, ASTRID: For all
these sins, O God of forgiveness,

911
00:38:38,305 --> 00:38:42,476
forgive us, pardon us,
and grant us atonement.

912
00:38:42,560 --> 00:38:45,938
[SINGING IN HEBREW]

913
00:38:46,022 --> 00:38:48,024
[CROWD SINGING ALONG]

914
00:38:50,193 --> 00:38:53,613
[RABBI, ASTRID HOLDING NOTE]

915
00:39:02,330 --> 00:39:04,415
[ASTRID HOLDS NOTE]

916
00:39:04,499 --> 00:39:07,126
[RABBI SPEAKING YIDDISH]

917
00:39:07,210 --> 00:39:11,213
-Here we go.
-[HORN BLOWS]

918
00:39:11,297 --> 00:39:13,508
[EXCITED CHATTER]

919
00:39:13,592 --> 00:39:15,510
-I have nuts in my purse.
-Over here. I… I'll take some.

920
00:39:15,594 --> 00:39:16,928
-If you have one left…
-What?

921
00:39:17,012 --> 00:39:18,138
I won't have one left.

922
00:39:18,222 --> 00:39:19,681
Get in here and fight for your nuts.

923
00:39:19,765 --> 00:39:21,141
-I'm gonna go ahead with Ethan.
-Hurry, hurry!

924
00:39:21,225 --> 00:39:23,268
See if I can hose him off before dinner.

925
00:39:23,352 --> 00:39:25,020
Papa, wait, wait.

926
00:39:25,104 --> 00:39:27,647
-I need to talk to you.
-Shirley's nuts will be gone.

927
00:39:27,731 --> 00:39:30,483
-I have to leave dinner by 9:00.
-What are you talking about?

928
00:39:30,567 --> 00:39:32,569
I have a very big show
tonight; it's at the Gaslight,

929
00:39:32,653 --> 00:39:34,446
and it's for a booker, and if I do well,

930
00:39:34,530 --> 00:39:36,781
it could mean more gigs, more money.

931
00:39:36,865 --> 00:39:38,867
-[SIGHS]
-I need you to cover for me.

932
00:39:38,951 --> 00:39:40,994
-Cover for you? It's Yom Kippur.
-Hey, you're the one

933
00:39:41,078 --> 00:39:42,455
who wanted me to keep
my stand-up career quiet.

934
00:39:42,539 --> 00:39:44,081
Now, does this not have to be a big deal.

935
00:39:44,165 --> 00:39:45,541
I've worked the whole thing out.

936
00:39:45,625 --> 00:39:47,501
Right after dessert, I'll
suddenly get a headache.

937
00:39:47,585 --> 00:39:50,213
I'll go lie down, and you
propose everybody play a game.

938
00:39:50,297 --> 00:39:52,506
Like <i>Name that Homicidal Despot?</i>

939
00:39:52,590 --> 00:39:54,342
Or charades.
Gather everyone in the living room,

940
00:39:54,426 --> 00:39:56,135
and say you want to go first,
then position yourself right

941
00:39:56,219 --> 00:39:57,803
in front of the fireplace.
That way, they'll have to face you

942
00:39:57,887 --> 00:39:59,305
and they'll have their
backs to the front door.

943
00:39:59,389 --> 00:40:00,973
That gives me a chance
to slip out unnoticed.

944
00:40:01,057 --> 00:40:02,391
Now, earlier, you would've
cracked the door open

945
00:40:02,475 --> 00:40:03,976
and put a pair of my shoes outside

946
00:40:04,060 --> 00:40:06,187
so I can tiptoe out barefoot
and no one will hear me.

947
00:40:06,271 --> 00:40:08,147
Later, when I get home,
I'll make an owl hoot sound,

948
00:40:08,231 --> 00:40:10,107
and you can come downstairs
and let me in the service entrance.

949
00:40:10,191 --> 00:40:11,525
-And then we can…
-Enough.

950
00:40:11,609 --> 00:40:13,153
I'm not playing charades,

951
00:40:13,237 --> 00:40:15,322
I'm not putting your
shoes outside the door,

952
00:40:15,406 --> 00:40:17,950
-or responding to your hooting.
-But…

953
00:40:18,034 --> 00:40:19,952
Tell them. Tell them what you're doing.

954
00:40:20,036 --> 00:40:21,536
It's time.

955
00:40:21,620 --> 00:40:23,705
Are you sure?

956
00:40:23,789 --> 00:40:26,416
I am not going to lie for
you right after Yom Kippur.

957
00:40:26,500 --> 00:40:28,502
I'm not gonna blow a
year's worth of sinning

958
00:40:28,586 --> 00:40:29,795
in the first two hours.

959
00:40:29,879 --> 00:40:32,047
Okay. If you say so.

960
00:40:32,131 --> 00:40:33,465
And not a word about me knowing

961
00:40:33,549 --> 00:40:35,008
about this stand-up thing ahead of time.

962
00:40:35,092 --> 00:40:37,761
-So you want me to lie.
-Like a Bible salesman.

963
00:40:37,845 --> 00:40:38,971
You want me to blow a year's worth

964
00:40:39,055 --> 00:40:40,347
of sinning in the first two hours.

965
00:40:40,431 --> 00:40:42,475
Sharp as a tack.
Now, do you have any more

966
00:40:42,559 --> 00:40:44,894
of Ethan's chocolate
in that purse of yours?

967
00:40:44,978 --> 00:40:45,778
MOISHE: We forgot Bubbabosia.

968
00:40:45,862 --> 00:40:47,188
SHIRLEY: Thank God
we tied her to the bench.

969
00:40:47,272 --> 00:40:49,065
This isn't gonna look
good with the guy upstairs.

970
00:40:49,149 --> 00:40:51,317
-Mr. Bussman? Why would he care?
-Just go.

971
00:40:51,401 --> 00:40:54,988
